FBIS4-62120 "drsov092_b_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Shakhray Reportedly To Be Replaced as Federation Minister Shakhray Reportedly To Be Replaced as Federation Minister LD1205084994 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 0800 GMT 12 May 94 LD1205084994 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy Russian BFN [Text] Our radio station has learned that the issue of releasing Sergey Shakhray from his duties as minister for federation affairs, while at the same time retaining him as vice premier, has almost been settled. By all accounts the new minister for federation affairs will be Nikolay Yegorov, currently Krasnodar kray head of administration and a member of the Federation Council . Sergey Shakhray has refused to confirm or deny this information.
